track_notes: This route is via the old access road for a cut-line. It is shorter and easier (no bush-wacking) than the route vis the Ole Buck look-out path from Sibbald Lake Campground.

The wooded slopes north of Hwy 68, have been logged, so the hike is a mix of logging road and slash. The summit is still treed (Jan 2024) but it is not clear how extensive the logging will be. Not a recommended hike.

The usual trail up Ole Buck (up the old cut-line) climbs over a ridge and then looses a lot of elevation before climbing to the summit. That trail also traverses a bowl on the lee-side of a N-S ridge, and in the winter the snow lies deep.
This trail up the south ridge climbs steadily up the N-S ridge and if you keep to the summit of the ridge, the snow is much less deep than it is on the lee-side.
Please note there is a small creek to cross close to the road, it was solidly frozen in March 2023.
While there is a lot of flagging on the ridge, it did not make much sense. Just keep to the top of the ridge.
Bell cell-phone service is available on the summit.
track_title: South Ridge has been logged Jan 2024
